items.name: Kazusa / カズサ / 카즈사 / 和纱 (Blue Archive)
items.description:
Kyouyama Kazusa (Blue Archive)

杏山カズサ (ブルーアーカイブ) / 쿄야마 카즈사 (블루 아카이브) / 杏山和纱 (碧蓝档案)

Usage

  • Use any or all of the following tags to summon Kazusa: kazusa, 1girl, animal ears, colored inner hair, halo, short hair

  • For her normal outfit: black choker, black jacket, black pantyhose, green sailor collar, hooded jacket, white skirt, miniskirt, hairclip, pink neckerchief, school uniform, sneakers

    • For a closed jacket, you might need to add open jacket, white shirt to the negative prompt.

    • For raised hood: hood up

  • For her "trying to look cool" expression: expressionless, blush, sweatdrop, v-shaped eyebrows, embarrassed

    • For selfies: selfie, (reaching towards viewer:1.2)

  • For eating: eating, :t, holding food, food on face

  • Accessories: macaron, cake, fork

Not all tags may be necessary. Kazusa has a lot of high quality art so I was able to curate a very large dataset. As a result it should be easy to change her outfit and hairstyle with different prompts.

I try to avoid overfitting my LoRAs. As a result, your prompt might require more tags to perfectly reproduce the character, but in exchange the model should be much more flexible when changing clothing or hairstyles and mixes well with other LoRAs and art styles. I recommend setting weight to 1.0 and using some of the tags provided above.

私はLoRAモデルのオーバーフィッティングを避けるようにしています。そのため、キャラクターを完全に再現するには、より多くのタグが必要になる場合がありますが、その代わり、モデルはキャラクターの衣服や髪型の変更に柔軟に対応でき、他のLoRAモデルやアートスタイルとも相性が良くなります。必要に応じて、重みを1.0に設定し、上記で提供したタグのいくつかを使用することをお勧めします。

저는 LoRA 모델을 오버피팅하는 것을 피하기 위해 노력합니다. 그 결과로, 캐릭터를 완벽하게 재현하기 위해서는 더 많은 태그가 필요할 수 있지만, 대신 모델은 캐릭터의 의상이나 머리 스타일을 쉽게 변경할 수 있으며, 다른 LoRA 모델 및 아트 스타일과도 잘 어울립니다. 가능한 태그 중 일부를 사용하고, 가중치를 1.0으로 설정하는 것을 권장합니다.

我尽量避免LoRA模型的过拟合。因此，你的提示可能需要更多的标签来完美地复现角色，但是相应地，该模型在更改角色服装或发型方面更加灵活，与其他LoRA模型和艺术风格混合得更好。我建议将权重设置为1.0，并使用上面提供的标签中的一些。

Refer to https://huggingface.co/khanon/lora-training for other Blue Archive characters, training parameters, and datasets.

items.name: Iori Yoshizuki - I''s
items.description:
If I said a quality waifu i would be lying. I''s is my least favorite Masakazu Katsura's Work. I was searching for images either from AI Amano(Videogirl AI) or Karin Aoi (DNA2) rather unsuccessfully until I found a very nice I''s doujin and what can i say I am a weak man.

Thus we got this... Iori is rather plain and the artwork is scarce and varies a lot. The anime style is almost completely different from Katsura's also.

V2

Another very old LORA retrain, as i mentioned in the old comment above, the anime screens were awful and the style didn't match in the slightest so i purged most of it. Other than that i did some more cleaning and re tagged everything.

Seems to work fine with: <lora:yoshizuki_ioriV2:0.7> yoshizuki_iori,

Was only able to isolate a single outfit:

  • School_uniform_Purple_shirt_Blue_skirt_White_neckerchief_Black_thighhighs: Her school uniform.

There was some more stuff in the anime but the style is extremely generic and doesn't reminds me of Katsura's work. Honestly Seishinja, Kuusou Zikken or redlight(Don't search for them if you have any type of sensibilities) make a much better job that the actual official anime.

Anyway as most of the Anime was purged form the dataset I will add it with the tag summary so people can experiment.

V1

Regardless... Effective wight seems to be between .4 and .7.

Got stable results with: <lora:Yoshizuki_Iori:0.55>, (Yoshizuki_Iori), big_breasts, bangs

*Edit: adding blush to the prompt might help, I was checking the tags and it was rather high. (<lora:Yoshizuki_Iori:0.55>, (Yoshizuki_Iori), big_breasts, bangs, blush)

At .45 it is a coin toss if the lora will accurately represent Katsura's style(got 1 out of 5 I could say "that's Iori" with confidence.). That's the problem with Iori being rather plain. At .65 it is more consistent but the doujin source might start to make things look granulated. Therefore I got best results at .55.

Surprisingly all training data was SFW even if it came from doujins, I just put this at NSFW just to be safe.

items.name: Extra Breasts: Triple Trouble
items.description:
BROKEN-ASS PRE-ALPHA

See 'How To Use' below. Results not guaranteed and may vary widely depending on prompt, model, seed, phase of the moon, and your opinion on skub.

Do you feel like the original Extra Breasts LoRA skipped a number somewhere? Do you totally recall a number of breasts that is greater than two, but less than four?

Well then, by popular demand, here's a LoRA designed to bring you back to that life-defining moment in 1990 when a Martian sex worker opened her top and revealed something incredible. (Or alternatively, to help you bring to life the visions sparked by the all-too-brief mentions of Eccentrica Gallumbits in the Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy series.)

How To Use

Does not require any trigger words, although having a female subject and 'breasts' somewhere in the prompt is recommended. Weight at 1.0 is recommended for both anime-styled and realistic gens; works slightly better with NAI/Anything-based models. Trained and tested mostly on images with vertical aspect ratios (2:3 to 8:11) so you're likely to get best results with those.

However: This thing will not work reliably with any clothing at all, tends to generate uncomfortably textured boobs on subjects with otherwise stylized super-smooth skin, frequently adds or subtracts a breast somewhere, is capable of relatively few angles and poses, and in general is hilariously unreliable.

But, like the first version of the original EB, once in a while it spits out some real magic.

I'm releasing this separately from the main EB for two reasons - 1, to prevent confusion about which version to use (this one can't do 4, at least not in the same way the original can), and 2, specifically because this thing is at least as broken as the first version of the original.

items.name: Valkyrae (streamer)
items.description:
General info

My first attempt at creating a Lora. Recently hopped on the SD bandwagon and learning as we go along.

Which version should you use?

There are 2 versions. V_portrait for most consistent likeness, but v_flex if you want to try and get a shot from a bit further away. You might get a good one.

Performance

At specific facial angles from up close it manages to capture her likeness fairly well. Quickly breaks down from farther away or odd side/back angles. Basically if it's from far away enough that you can see below the chest, the likeness usually just isn't there (or maybe I just can't bring it out).

Strength

Starts convincing me at strengths 0.7 and up, but your mileage may vary. Sometimes I get a lucky roll with 0.5 strength.

Side notes

In a lot of the training images she was wearing a choker/necklace. Add choker, necklace to your negative prompt to try and mitigate this if you don't want them in your images.

She might look a bit young sometimes, because some training images are from when she was younger.

If your images don't turn out exactly like the sample images, even when copying the generation data, it might be because you're running Stable Diffusion with xformers enabled. This sacrifices reproducibility on the same seed for faster image generation. Sample images were generated with xformers disabled.

modelVersions.name: v_portrait
modelVersions.description: Trained on face crops only. Heavily prefers super closeup portrait type images. Definitely the best at capturing her likeness up close. Not very flexible and will turn almost any image into super close up. Try adding closeup, portrait or similar words to your negative prompt to fight the Lora.

modelVersions.name: v_flex
modelVersions.description: Trained on photos cropped from head to shoulder/bust height. More flexible and interferes less with the rest of your prompt. Likeness is a bit of a hit or miss though, but keep rolling and you might get a few ones that look a lot like her.

Alfamix is great for creating book covers, album covers, intricate landscapes and rich art. It's also good for detailed portraits. You can create highly detailed images. See examples and prompts.

The model can also work on small steps, but use 100-150 steps + Hires. fix for best results.

items.name: Kemono Friends Official Style
items.description:
Animal frens in the style of Yoshizaki Mine.

About this LoRA
This LoRA is trained on 61 images of official chibi(ish) art on as many characters from Kemono Friends. Despite having only one image per character it works pretty well to prompt most of them using just their name. If you want more accuracy add tags describing the character further, see the uploaded list of tags.
By not using a name of a specific fren it can also be used as a general style LoRA to make cute Kemono Friends knockoffs.

How to use
Base prompt: 1girl, [character name] (see below),
Recommended strength: 0.7 to 1.0 depending on model, prompt, other LoRAs etc
If you're after a result best matching the official chibi art use a model with good medium and drawing technique tag support. Base NAI works if you have nothing else on hand.

Misc
512 resolution trained on NAI without noise offset option for best LoRA compatibility. Dataset of based on 61 images.
Tested on NAI + AOM2.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

Below are all characters trained in this LoRA. The list also doubles as a wildcard generator for users of the AUTOMATIC1111 release.

items.name: [SD 1.5] Pokemon - Gardenia / Natane
items.description:
Please read through the entire description (might need to be expanded) and the version change notes as they cover a lot of information about basic use cases and limitations. The description is always focused on the latest version. Thank you!

This is an SD 1.5 LoRA for the character Gardenia / Natane from Pokemon. It works for models based on SD 1.x only, it will not work for models based on SD 2.x or SDXL!

Example images were picked from pure 512x512 txt2img results and then re-created at 1024x1024 using txt2img with moderate Hi-res Fix settings (upscaler Lanczos, denoising strength 0.4). This improves faces and other details that are almost impossible to get correctly and consistently at 512x512 (limitation of the technology) while still giving a realistic impression of what it looks like. Pure 512x512 results will have more distorted faces and less detail.

Please see the version change notes for the training and example image generation models as well as the used weights as they might change between versions. Remember that you might need to adjust weights to best suit your use case!

Remember to add the tag gardenia \(pokemon\) (with backslashes intact) to your positive prompt.

The training set contained multiple variations of Gardenia's signature look (although very limited and heavily biased towards the classic look because of limited usable training data) so you might need to put combinations of the following tags in your positive or negative prompts to get the desired results:

  • poncho

  • cropped shirt

  • midriff

  • belt

  • shorts

  • boots

As the training set contained a few images with floating hair, you might need to add floating hair to the negative prompts if not desired.

Known Limitations / Problems:

  • The boots were not present in a lot of images and not a focus for the training so they sadly will not be consistent at all.

  • Loves to generate black legwear under the shorts for some reason (not part of any training image). Try adding black legwear to the negative prompts. Might still show up a lot though.

  • The shorts might come out longer than expected, especially from behind, and are often not torn. Maybe torn shorts in the positive prompts might help with this but I've not tried it a lot.

  • For some tag combinations, the hair might suddenly come out as long. Try adding short hair to the positive prompts for those cases (does not seem to happen often though).

  • Shots from behind are very inconsistent due to extremely limited training data. Might for instance generate the poncho pattern, not apply poses correctly etc. Not much I can do without a bit more training data.

modelVersions.name: v3
modelVersions.description:
There are detailed changes below the next paragraph, you might need to expand this version changes box!

I learned a few new things about creating LoRAs and wanted to see how far I can push my existing LoRAs without changes to their datasets. So there's still no support for alternate outfits, colors etc. for now, sorry! There are other LoRAs if you want those things. Not sure if I'll improve the LoRAs more than that in the future or make new ones but who knows.

LoRA Changes:

  • Now uses the standard "gardenia \(pokemon\)" instead of a custom trigger word to make things easier for everyone (please note though that the LoRA itself is still named "character_pokemon_gardenia_vX" as before!)

  • Switch to 32 dims (now trained directly instead of resizing from 128)

  • Switch to target weight 1 (increased from 0.7)

  • Changed a lot of training settings (too many to list, check LoRA metadata if you are interested) and updated to much newer scripts version (~3 months worth of changes)

Example image changes:

  • Use CLIP skip 2 instead of 1 as I accidentally did before

  • Change settings for hir-res fix: Switch upscaler from None to Lanczos and increase denoise from 0.1 to 0.4 to get better results while still not changing TOO much

  • Use a negative embedding for the majority of negative prompting

Recommended weight: 1

Training model: Anything V3

Example image generation model: AbyssOrangeMix2 - Hardcore

modelVersions.name: v2
modelVersions.description:
General changes:

  • Changed example weight from ~0.5 to ~0.7 (result of training changes)

Changes to the training process (with the goal of hopefully making this and my other models more flexible and compatible while reducing overfitting):

  • Switched from a flat 200 repeats x 1 epoch to 20 repeats x 10 epochs (max) and selecting the best results

  • Lowered network training alpha from 128 to 64 to hopefully increase the quality of the result a bit

  • Resized LoRA from rank 128 to rank 64 rank after training (still training with rank 128) to reduce size and "smooth out" some of the training results while not changing much (going down to rank 32 seems to have too much influence on the quality of results, so I kept it at 64)

Used weight: 0.7

Training model: Anything V3

Example image generation model: AbyssOrangeMix2 - Hardcore

items.name: HoloMyth All in one LORA | Hololive
items.description:
I am using AbyssOrangeMix3 (AOM3)

A weight at around ~0.7-0.9 is recommended, but other weights may also work in certain situations. Just play around with it and use what feels right to you. The weight also differs from character to character. For example Ina needs a bit more, while Ame can do just fine on lower weights.

The prompts are: "Amelia Watson, Calliope Mori, Gawr Gura, Ina'nis Ninomae, Kiara Takanashi".

If you find that the characteristics mix, try adding other character names to the negative prompts.

Let me know if you have any problems!
You can reach me either in the comments or on reddit.

使用了人物描述以后也可以生成人形。

This is a Lora of the Chinese zodiac signs. You can control it with tags such as pig, bear, chook, monkey, sheep, horse, snake, dragon, bunny, tiger, cow, rat, etc.
It is difficult to change the scene, so you need to add more weight.
I'm using sunshinemix_sunlightmixPruned
fter using character description, it is also possible to generate humanoid
The Lora model goes under this folder: \extensions\ sd-webue-additional -networks\models\lora

items.name: 宇佐見蓮子/宇佐见莲子/Usami Renko - Touhou Project
items.description:
宇佐见莲子的LoRA模型，属于是我尝试训练LoRA模型的初作，但之后训练的LoRA的质量似乎比这个还不如呢（笑）。

The LoRA model of Usami Renko. This is the first outcome of my attempt to train a LoRA, although the following works are not as good as this one.

一般权重在0.8-1。我强烈建议加入一些外貌的详细prompt来稳定该模型的表现，以下是我常用的prompt：

The recommended weight is 0.8~1. I strongly suggest adding more detailed prompts on appearance to stabilize the outcome. These are the prompts I often use:

renko, black victorian hat, short black hair, black capelet, red tie, white shirt, black pleated skirt, white socks, black dress shoes,
